name: language_sql_data_block_comment_opener
description: |
  Slash-star can open an SQL block comment if a value escapes its intended
  literal or identifier context. It also catches sanitizers that strip
  comment-looking text from legitimate data.
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: ascii
pair:
  - with: block-comment-closer.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "language"
  - "sql"
  - "sql-data"
  - "string"
  - "block-comment"
  - "escaping"
  - "injection-canary"
---
/*
